    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    ActiveActor
    This class represents an active actor in the game.
    ActiveActorDestructible
    An abstract class that represents an actor that can be destroyed.
    Boss
    Represents the boss enemy in the game.
    BossProjectile
    A class representing a projectile fired by the boss.
    CollisionHandler
    Handles collisions between actors in the game.
    Controller
    Controller class to control the game.
    Destructible
    Interface for objects that can take damage and be destroyed.
    EnemyPlane
    Class for the enemy plane.
    EnemyProjectile
    Class for enemy projectiles.
    FighterPlane
    Abstract class for fighter planes.
    GameOverScreen
    This class creates the game over screen that is displayed when the player loses the game.
    HeartDisplay
    Class that represents the display of the hearts in the game.
    LevelFour
    Level four of the game.
    LevelOne
    LevelOne class that extends LevelParent and represents the first level of the game.
    LevelParent
    This class is the parent class for all levels in the game.
    LevelThree
    Level three of the game.
    LevelTwo
    Level two of the game.
    LevelView
    This class is responsible for displaying the game elements on the screen.
    LevelViewLevelFour
    Level view for level four.
    Main
    Main class to start the game.
    MainMenu
    Main menu for the game.
    MovementHandler
    Class to handle the movement of the user plane.
    Projectile
    Abstract class for projectiles.
    ShieldImage
    Class to represent the shield image.
    UserPlane
    Class representing the user-controlled plane.
    UserProjectile
    Interface for objects that can take damage and be destroyed.
    WinImage
    Class to display the win image.
